---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Liechtenstein Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/liechtenstein/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Switzerland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/switzerland' },
  { title: 'Austria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/austria' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'liechtensteinFit', header: 'Liechtenstein Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CHF$480-685/mo', liechtensteinFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CHF$560-800/mo', liechtensteinFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CHF$430-615/mo', liechtensteinFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Swiss Insurance', entryAge: 'Various', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CHF$500-750/mo', liechtensteinFit: 'Standard' },
  { provider: 'OKP (Mandatory)', entryAge: 'All ages', renewal: 'Required', monthlyFrom: 'CHF$350-500/mo', liechtensteinFit: 'Required' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'OKP (Mandatory Basic)', monthly: 'CHF$350-500', annual: 'CHF$4,200-6,000' },
  { category: 'Supplementary (65-69)', monthly: 'CHF$430-685', annual: 'CHF$5,160-8,220' },
  { category: 'Supplementary (70-74)', monthly: 'CHF$590-915', annual: 'CHF$7,080-10,980' },
  { category: 'Supplementary (75-79)', monthly: 'CHF$790-1,225', annual: 'CHF$9,480-14,700' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'CHF$150-300/visit', annual: 'Swiss quality' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Liechtenstein 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Liechtenstein. Alpine principality, Swiss healthcare access, tax advantages, and coverage for affluent retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Liechtenstein"
  subheadline="Liechtenstein offers Alpine beauty, exceptional safety, low taxes, Swiss healthcare access, and German-speaking community—a tiny wealthy principality ideal for affluent retirees seeking privacy and stability."
  heroImage="/images/countries/liechtenstein-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Liechtenstein</h2>
  <p>
    Liechtenstein offers a unique combination of Alpine scenery, Swiss-level healthcare access, low taxes (flat 1.2% income tax), exceptional safety, German language, and privacy. For affluent retirees seeking stability, natural beauty, and tax efficiency in a tight-knit community, Liechtenstein provides unique advantages.
  </p>

  <p>
    Vaduz is the capital. Triesen and Triesenberg offer village living. Entire country is 160 km²—walkable scale. Zürich is 1.5 hours away; Innsbruck 2 hours. Population only 40,000. Residency is competitive and limited.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Local clinic; Swiss hospitals accessible</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> German (Alemannic dialect)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> CHF$4,000-8,000/month; expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Alpine; cold winters; pleasant summers</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Quiet; private; traditional</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> Flat 1.2% income tax; favorable</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Liechtenstein Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Liechtenstein has mandatory health insurance (OKP) similar to Switzerland. Liechtenstein National Hospital (Landesspital) in Vaduz handles routine care. Complex cases go to Swiss hospitals—Kantonsspital Graubünden (Chur), Universitätsspital Zürich. Healthcare access effectively Swiss-quality through formal agreements.
  </p>

  <p>
    OKP is mandatory basic insurance. Supplementary insurance covers private rooms, choice of doctor, alternative medicine. Swiss hospitals are 1-2 hours away for specialized care. System works seamlessly with Switzerland.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">OKP Is Mandatory</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      All Liechtenstein residents must have OKP basic insurance. Choose from approved insurers. Supplementary insurance adds private coverage. Swiss hospitals accessible through agreements. Budget for both basic OKP and supplementary coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Liechtenstein residency is restrictive:
  </p>

  <h3>Residency Permit</h3>
  <p>
    Very limited—Liechtenstein restricts immigration. Non-EEA nationals face strict quotas. Requires proof of self-sufficiency, housing, and typically employment or substantial wealth. Waiting lists exist.
  </p>

  <h3>EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    EEA nationals have easier access through bilateral agreements. Still requires proof of financial independence for retirees. Quotas apply.
  </p>

  <h3>Wealth Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    No official minimum but expect substantial assets (€1M+) and income proof. Character references important. Small community is selective.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Liechtenstein:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>OKP:</strong> Mandatory basic coverage for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Supplementary:</strong> Highly recommended for seniors</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage:</strong> Must cover Liechtenstein and Switzerland</li>
    <li><strong>Providers:</strong> Choose from approved insurers</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Liechtenstein</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Two-layer system: OKP basic (mandatory) plus supplementary insurance. Supplementary covers private rooms, Swiss clinic choice, dental, and alternative medicine. International coverage useful for travel. System similar to Swiss model.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Liechtenstein, Swiss-quality coverage expected:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Liechtenstein</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong European network, Swiss access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Swiss insurers:</strong> Seamless local integration</li>
    <li><strong>Quality standards:</strong> Must match Swiss expectations</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Liechtenstein with Swiss access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Liechtenstein (CHF):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Total Healthcare Budget</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>OKP + Supplementary:</strong> CHF$800-1,200/month typical</li>
    <li><strong>Swiss quality:</strong> Premium costs for premium care</li>
    <li><strong>Tax advantages:</strong> Low income tax offsets some costs</li>
    <li><strong>Wealthy residents:</strong> Comprehensive coverage standard</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: German Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €6,000/month pension. EEA citizen. Hiking enthusiast.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> OKP + Cigna Global supplementary.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~CHF$850/month. Alpine lifestyle; Swiss hospital access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Wealthy Privacy-Seeker, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €15,000/month. Non-EEA. Vaduz residence.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> OKP + BUPA Global premium.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~CHF$1,100/month. Premium coverage; maximum privacy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Swiss Neighbor, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> CHF$8,000/month. Former Zürich resident. Tax optimization.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> OKP + local supplementary.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~CHF$750/month. Familiar system; tax advantages.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can non-EU citizens get residency?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult—Liechtenstein has strict quotas. Non-EEA nationals face long waiting lists. Exceptional circumstances (significant investment, family ties) may help. Most successful applicants are EEA nationals or extremely wealthy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use Swiss hospitals?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—formal agreements ensure access to Swiss healthcare. Kantonsspital Graubünden (Chur) is closest major hospital. Zürich hospitals accessible for complex care. Insurance covers cross-border treatment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does the tax benefit work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Flat 1.2% income tax (plus municipal surcharge ~4-7% total). No wealth tax. Favorable for high earners compared to Switzerland or Germany. Professional tax advice essential for planning.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Liechtenstein boring?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very quiet—population 40,000, traditional Alpine community. Beautiful for hiking, skiing. Cultural events limited. Zürich and Innsbruck provide city access. Best for those seeking peace, nature, and privacy over nightlife.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Liechtenstein coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Liechtenstein residency is highly restricted with quotas. Always verify current requirements with Liechtenstein authorities and consult with professional advisors.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
